review_title: Great easy way to mount your phone.
reviews:
Easy install and strong magnets. Comes with duplicates of everything so you get 2 mounts and 4 magnetic plates.

The magnetic force is really strong. I stuck the magnet on my case and it does not move during bumpy rides. Placing it inbetween the case and phone does work for slimmer cases, but I am using the spigen rugged case and it is too thick and the magnet needs to be stuck on the outside of the case

I've had this type of case for my lg g6 and now pixel 2 xl and it is what I expected out of Spigen.

Provides great protection for your phone with dual layers and a raised lip to protect the screen. It does add a little bulk, but it is the cost of extra protection/peace of mind. Also looks very sleek

Spigen is a real force in the cellphone accessory market. I also have their magnetic car mount which I paired with this case. NOTE: this case is thick so putting the magnet inside the case does not provide the enough sticking force to the mount. I stuck the magnet right on the outside of the case and it really sticks.

review_title: Great alternative to name brand shift stops
reviews:
Overall the install was fairly easy (this was my first mod that I've ever installed, so pretty easy if you're a handy guy). It took about 45 minutes. There are tons of tutorials on YouTube which is where I learned.

I'm going to say this product makes a noticeable different when shifting 1st and 2nd. It doesn't remove all the notchyness, but it does make it A LOT smoother

I would recommend this product. I've never tried a Perrin shift stop, but why buy something that cost 50% more for a product that works just as well.

Note: installed on my 2018 Subaru WRX base

I write this review almost half a year later to say that the SSD randomly died. Explored most options until confirming that this is true because chkdsk.exe would crash not completing the scan. Reformatting/Resetting the SSD would also not crash the PC.

Now this may just be a singular event, but until this point, this SSD was working perfectly. Maybe its just bad luck.
As advertised. Except the squeeky thing is broken! No squeeky. Would like a refund or a working product

review_title: Loved the "fat" flipped part of the beanie
reviews: Loved the "fat" flipped part of the beanie. It appears to be well made, with a medium-weight fabric that is also very stretchy. It's what I expected it to be. Has somewhat of a street wear look to it, but I can also see this worn as a normal toque. Will buy another in black and maybe some other colour.
